EcoNest Privacy Policy
Effective Date: [Insert Date]

EcoNest (“the Skill”) is designed to help you control and optimize your smart home devices through Amazon Alexa. We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information.

Information Collection
EcoNest does not collect, store, or share personal information outside of the Alexa ecosystem.

Any data processed (such as device status or commands) remains within Amazon’s Alexa services.

We do not request or store account credentials, payment information, or personally identifiable data.

Information Use
Data exchanged with EcoNest is used solely to provide smart home functionality (e.g., turning devices on/off, adjusting thermostats).

EcoNest does not use your information for marketing, advertising, or analytics.

Information Sharing
EcoNest does not share your information with third parties.

All interactions are handled through Amazon Alexa’s secure platform.

Security
EcoNest relies on Amazon’s Alexa infrastructure for secure data transmission.

We do not maintain independent servers or databases that store your information.

User Rights
You may disable EcoNest at any time through the Alexa app.

Disabling the skill immediately stops all data exchange between EcoNest and Alexa.

